text: Kongur Tagh is a mountain in the Pamir range, in China. It is also known as Kongkoerh. It is the 37th highest mountain in the world. The first people to reach the top were Peter Boardman, Chris Bonington, Alan Rouse, and loe Tasker, in 1981. ==References== Category:Mountains of Xinjiang
title: Kongur Tagh
